  • Method Details

    • addAndRemoveTracks

      public void addAndRemoveTracks(List<String> tracksToAdd, List<String> tracksToRemove) throws FatalRequestResponse
      Function which allows you to add and remove tracks through the Spotify API. Adding and removing tracks has been merged to better suit the Spotify api. Due to Spotify's implementation, tracks are first removed and then added. This method will throw an exception if you are not allowed to make modifications to this playlist. Check canModify() beforehand.
      Parameters:
      tracksToAdd - The tracks to add to the playlist (nullable).
      tracksToRemove - The tracks to remove from the playlist (nullable)
      Throws:
      FatalRequestResponse

    • shuffleInPlace

      public void shuffleInPlace() throws FatalRequestResponse
      Shuffles the playlist's tracks in-place. Internally this is done by moving songs at random to the front, ensuring that every song is only reordered once. This method will throw an exception if the user of the api this playlist is linked to is not the owner of this playlist. This method will throw an exception if you are not allowed to make modifications to this playlist. Check canModify() beforehand.
      Throws:
      FatalRequestResponse

    • canModify

      public boolean canModify()
      Check whether you are allowed to make modifications to this playlist. Calling a modifying function on this playlist while not being allowed to modify it will result in exceptions.
      Returns:
      True if modifications are allowed, false otherwise.
